entries.meaning: Not having been sanctified; not made sacred; remaining mundane or worldly. #*  1837,  L[etitia] E[lizabeth] L[andon],  Ethel Churchill: Or, The Two Brides. […], volume I, London: Henry Colburn, […], →OCLC, pages 154–155:They forced me into a convent, whence your father rescued me: and that evening I was married to him—ay, married. A daughter of my noble house could not have stooped to a love unsanctified by duty.
